.TH GENUP 1 "December 2025" "Gentoo System Updater" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
genup \- Gentoo System Updater
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B genup
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B genup
is a comprehensive system update tool for Gentoo Linux that automates the entire
process of updating your system, including:
.PP
.IP \(bu 2
Synchronizing the Portage tree and eix cache
.IP \(bu 2
Updating all packages in the @world set
.IP \(bu 2
Handling configuration file conflicts with dispatch\-conf
.IP \(bu 2
Rebuilding external kernel modules
.IP \(bu 2
Updating kernel (with buildkernel support)
.IP \(bu 2
Cleaning up orphaned packages and old source files
.IP \(bu 2
Running custom updater scripts
.PP
The script is designed to be run interactively but can also operate in automated
mode with appropriate command line options.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-a, \-\-ask
Turn on interactive mode: require user confirmation for key actions.
.TP
.B \-A, \-\-alert
Sound terminal bell when interaction is required. Automatically enables \-\-ask.
.TP
.B \-b, \-\-buildkernel\-args=\fIARGS\fR
Pass additional arguments to the initial buildkernel invocation (requires
buildkernel USE flag).
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-dispatch\-conf
Run dispatch\-conf even in non\-interactive mode.
.TP
.B \-C, \-\-no\-custom\-updaters
Do not run custom updaters from /etc/genup/updaters.d directory.
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-deploy\-from\-staging
If a kernel is built successfully, deploy it to the EFI system partition
(requires buildkernel USE flag).
.TP
.B \-e, \-\-emerge\-args=\fIARGS\fR
Pass additional arguments to the main emerge command.
.TP
.B \-E, \-\-no\-emtee
Do not attempt to use emtee even when the emtee USE flag is enabled.
.TP
.B \-g, \-\-pgmerge
Try to use pgmerge for updates (experimental feature).
.TP
.B \-F, \-\-no\-fixups
Do not run /etc/cron.weekly/fixup script (aarch64 systems only).
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-i, \-\-ignore\-required\-changes
Do not exit with error if user configuration changes are required.
.TP
.B \-k, \-\-keep\-old\-distfiles
Do not purge old source tarballs (distfiles).
.TP
.B \-m, \-\-no\-eix\-metadata\-update
Do not update eix metadata at completion.
.TP
.B \-M, \-\-no\-module\-rebuild
Do not rebuild external modules.
.TP
.B \-n, \-\-no\-kernel\-upgrade
Do not attempt kernel upgrades (implied if buildkernel USE flag not set).
.TP
.B \-N, \-\-no\-nocache
Do not use nocache even when nocache USE flag is enabled.
.TP
.B \-p, \-\-no\-perl\-cleaner
Do not run perl\-cleaner.
.TP
.B \-r, \-\-adjustment=\fIN\fR
Set build niceness adjustment (-20 to 19, default: 19).
.TP
.B \-S, \-\-no\-eix\-sync
Do not run emaint sync or eix\-sync.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Display more detailed information.
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Display version number and exit.
.TP
.B \-x, \-\-eix\-sync\-args=\fIARGS\fR
Pass additional arguments to eix\-sync.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.PP
The behavior of genup can be customized through configuration files:
.PP
.I /etc/genup/genup.conf
.RS
Main configuration file with default settings.
.RE
.PP
.I /etc/genup/updaters.d/
.RS
Directory containing custom updater scripts that are executed after
system updates complete.
.RE
.SH USE FLAGS
.PP
The following USE flags can be set when emerging genup:
.TP
.B buildkernel
Enable kernel update support using buildkernel tool.
.TP
.B emtee
Enable support for the emtee package manager tool.
.TP
.B pgmerge
Enable support for the pgmerge package manager tool (experimental).
.TP
.B nocache
Enable support for the nocache filesystem caching tool.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Basic system update:
.RS
.B genup
.RE
.PP
Interactive system update with confirmations:
.RS
.B genup \-\-ask
.RE
.PP
System update with verbose output:
.RS
.B genup \-\-verbose
.RE
.PP
Update with custom emerge arguments:
.RS
.B genup \-\-emerge\-args="--autounmask-write"
.RE
.PP
Update without kernel upgrade:
.RS
.B genup \-\-no\-kernel\-upgrade
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.TP
.B TERM
Terminal type for color output and terminal control sequences.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/genup/genup.conf
Main configuration file.
.TP
.I /etc/genup/updaters.d/
Directory for custom updater scripts.
.TP
.I /etc/portage/postsync.d/eix
Portage postsync hook for eix updates (if eix version >= 0.36.7\-r2).
